nodes.bodyText:
I guess the original way
  @Override
  public void close() throws IOException {
    try {
      if (mClient.get().isShutdown()) {
        return;
      }
      mStream.close();
      mStream.waitForComplete(mDataTimeoutMs);
    } finally {
      mMarshaller.close();
      mClient.close();
    }
  }

is used instead of the closer to guarantee the close sequence. The mStream is always close before mClient. So if mClient is shutdown, we know that stream is closed as well.
in that case, may be better to keep the original way of closing items.

